[5] Cholera - Nigeria (Delta State)
Date: Tue 23 Jan 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Daily Sun [edited]
<http://www.sunnewsonline.com/webpages/news/national/2007/jan/23/national-23-01-2007-06.htm>

At least 5 persons have been confirmed dead in Bomadi local
government area of the Delta State following an outbreak of cholera
in the area last week. The Sun gathered yesterday, 22 Jan 2007, that
several others were on a danger list at the various health centers in
the council area as a result of the disease.
Unless the state government deploys more medical personnel, more
deaths are likely to be recorded this week, health authorities
warned. Investigations revealed that health officials in the council
area could not cope with the large numbers of patients arising from
the cholera outbreak.
Dr Emmanuel Enegbere confirmed the outbreak of the disease,
explaining that all the patients brought to the center had cholera.
He said 5 persons were brought to the health center already dead,
while several others were lying critically ill in various health
centers in the council area.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Nigeria's Delta State can be found in the southern part of the
country east of the capital Lagos area at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/nigeria.pdf>.
- Mod.LL]
