[7] Cholera - Kenya (Northeastern Province)
Date: Sun 21 Jan 2007
From: SK Sharif <sksharif@africaonline.co.ke>

The District Medical Officer of Health of Mandera District of
Northeastern Province has confirmed an outbreak of cholera in the
district. A family of 5 was admitted to the hospital with history of
bloody diarrhea on 14 Jan 2007. Samples taken to Nairobi confirmed
cholera. There have been 2 deaths, while the other 3 were treated and
discharged. No new cases of cholera have been reported since 14 Jan 2007.
--
Dr. SK Sharif
Chief Medical Specialist
Ministry of Health, Kenya
<sksharif@africaonline.co.ke>
[ProMED thanks Dr. Sharif for his continued contributions. A map of
Kenya showing the Northeastern Province can be found at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/kenya.pdf>.
As noted in the post preceding this one, the municipality of Mandera
(also spelled Mandhera) is on the border with Somalia. - Mod.LL]
