[8] Cholera - Angola (Cabinda)
Date: Fri 19 Jan 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=503067>

14 cases of cholera were registered in the past 24 hours in the
Provincial Hospital of Cabinda, ANGOP learned this Fri 19 Jan 2007
from the head of the department of public health and control of
endemic diseases, Razao Simao. 40 patients are currently hospitalized
in one of the 2 units specialized for the treatment of cholera.
Since the 1st case in May 2006, about 1580 cases were registered,
from which 40 resulted in death, mainly adults, due to the fact that
most refused to drink treated water, claiming that it tasted bad.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The Province of Cabinda can be found on a map of Angola at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf>.
As can be seen, the Province is not adjacent to the other parts of
Angola but rather north of them, bordered by Congo and Congo DR.
- Mod.LL]
