[9] Cholera - Angola (Luanda)
Date: Tue 23 Jan 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and Angola Press Agency (Luanda) [edited]

Over 200 cases of cholera, including 5 deaths, were reported from 1
to 22 Jan 2007 in Luanda, the provincial director for public health,
Isilda Neves, said on Tue 23 Jan 2007. The health director added that
the number might increase due to the last rains that fell in the
Angolan capital.
Health Deputy Minister Jose Van-Dunem said that in order to face the
situation, authorities will increase the supply of drinkable water to
residents in rain-hit areas.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Luanda is the capital of Angola, on the coast, see map at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf>. - Mod.JW]

